00:37.207 --> 00:38.925
JESSICA: How are the numbers?

00:39.767 --> 00:41.086
MARTIN: Incredible.

00:42.007 --> 00:45.477
(CHUCKLES) Absolutely incredible.

00:48.047 --> 00:49.605
Congratulations.

00:51.447 --> 00:53.005
I'm leaving you.

00:56.887 --> 00:58.923
Did you hear what I said?

00:59.247 --> 01:00.839
I'm leaving you.

01:01.047 --> 01:03.277
Yeah, I heard. Yeah. Yeah.

01:06.007 --> 01:08.202
- I'm not kidding.
- I know.

01:12.247 --> 01:15.557
Look, I think
it's an excellent decision on your part.

01:16.607 --> 01:17.801
You do?

01:17.967 --> 01:21.004
You're a fantastic person,

01:22.967 --> 01:25.561
and the last year's been great, really.

01:26.487 --> 01:28.125
You're beautiful.

01:28.767 --> 01:30.564
The sex has been wonderful.

01:30.647 --> 01:32.763
You're kind and supportive.

01:33.087 --> 01:36.477
You wait for me with dinner
when I work late, you're amazing.

01:36.567 --> 01:39.877
And it's driving me out of my fucking mind!

01:43.407 --> 01:44.476
You know, with numbers like this,

01:44.567 --> 01:46.046
this should be the happiest day of my life,

01:46.127 --> 01:50.200
and instead I have to worry about
whether I make you happy all the time!

01:53.447 --> 01:55.165
Jessica, sweetheart,

01:57.327 --> 02:00.160
you make me feel like being a better person.

02:00.247 --> 02:02.283
And I'm not a better person.

02:03.847 --> 02:05.075
I'm me.

02:07.847 --> 02:09.598
I feel sorry for you.

02:14.887 --> 02:16.161
Don't.

02:16.967 --> 02:18.639
I certainly don't.

02:22.087 --> 02:24.362
In fact, I envy myself deeply.

03:32.847 --> 03:34.565
- Morning.
- AGENT: Morning.

03:38.447 --> 03:40.199
Good morning, Mr President.

03:40.287 --> 03:42.243
And congratulations.

03:42.327 --> 03:44.966
It's good to have you with us
for another four years.

03:45.047 --> 03:47.686
Thank you, Thomas. It's good to be back.

03:48.527 --> 03:51.280
Would you like me to turn on the TV, sir?

03:53.327 --> 03:55.921
Oh, no. That's okay.

03:57.327 --> 03:59.045
STATON: Hey, I'll tell you what.

03:59.487 --> 04:02.001
- How about the paper?
- The paper, sir?

04:02.207 --> 04:04.437
Yeah. What the heck?

04:04.847 --> 04:08.317
We'll see what the New York Times
has to say about things.

04:08.687 --> 04:11.121
Bet they're eating some crow this morning.

04:11.207 --> 04:13.084
We have a copy anywhere?

04:13.167 --> 04:14.600
We can get one, sir.

04:14.687 --> 04:18.043
All right, get one.
And scare up my reading glasses.

04:19.487 --> 04:21.762
I'm going to read the newspaper.

04:22.167 --> 04:24.237
Shall I bring it to the workout room, sir?

04:24.327 --> 04:27.603
No, I'm gonna read my paper
right here in bed.

04:27.847 --> 04:29.724
Take it a little easy this morning.

04:29.807 --> 04:31.763
Well, you deserve it, sir.

04:31.847 --> 04:34.520
Yes, I do. It was a heck of a fight.

04:34.847 --> 04:36.724
Yes, sir, a heck of a fight.

04:36.807 --> 04:40.197
The important thing is the good guys won.

04:54.167 --> 04:55.680
(GRUNTING)

05:00.767 --> 05:01.961
Cut!

05:14.367 --> 05:15.482
Cut!

05:15.567 --> 05:16.886
(GROANS)

05:28.567 --> 05:29.636
(SPITTING)

05:29.727 --> 05:30.796
Cut!

05:32.287 --> 05:35.165
DIRECTOR: This guy is pathetic!
He's ruining every shot!

05:35.767 --> 05:37.246
You, come here!

05:38.567 --> 05:40.364
- I'm sorry, sir.
- Sorry?

05:40.447 --> 05:41.516
Is that what you're going to say

05:41.607 --> 05:43.757
when you endanger your brothers
on the holy mission?

05:43.847 --> 05:46.156
- No.
- Just stay out of the shot.

05:47.447 --> 05:48.721
Yes, sir.

05:49.287 --> 05:52.723
My wife's cousin.
Otherwise, I send him back home tomorrow!

05:53.207 --> 05:56.085
Okay, everybody, from the top, huh?
Let's shoot this puppy!

05:56.167 --> 05:57.441
Come on. Come on.

06:36.887 --> 06:38.605
(ONE PLAYING)

06:51.287 --> 06:52.481
(SINGING) One, pah!

06:53.047 --> 06:54.958
Singular sensation

06:55.047 --> 06:57.277
Every little step she takes

06:58.727 --> 07:00.001
One, pah!

07:00.647 --> 07:02.478
Thrilling combination

07:02.567 --> 07:05.035
Every move that she makes

07:06.727 --> 07:10.003
OMER: One smile and suddenly nobody

07:10.087 --> 07:12.647
else will do

07:14.247 --> 07:17.045
You know you'll never be lonely

07:17.127 --> 07:19.846
With you-know-who

07:21.367 --> 07:23.597
One moment

07:23.687 --> 07:24.722
Oh!

07:24.807 --> 07:26.240
What is this?

07:26.327 --> 07:27.726
Was I being loud?

07:27.807 --> 07:30.082
You could hear it down into the valley.

07:30.727 --> 07:32.080
Hey...

07:34.407 --> 07:35.760
That was rare.

07:35.847 --> 07:37.246
You are lucky it was me who found you,

07:37.327 --> 07:40.046
not one of the others
because they would cut your throat!

07:40.127 --> 07:42.880
I'm so sorry. I like show tunes.

07:43.327 --> 07:46.956
I grew up listening to them,
my mother had a collection of 50 records.

07:47.047 --> 07:49.242
Your mother was killed
by an American bomb.

07:49.327 --> 07:50.646
I know that.

07:51.087 --> 07:52.839
That is why I'm here.

07:53.047 --> 07:55.686
Look, I've got some news for you.

07:56.167 --> 07:57.600
Your papers came through.

07:57.687 --> 08:00.997
You are leaving next week for Frankfurt,
and from there to Orange County.

08:01.087 --> 08:04.318
You'll be staying at our mutual cousins'.
They know nothing of your purpose there.

08:04.407 --> 08:07.604
You are to just wait
until your sleeper cell contacts you.

08:07.687 --> 08:09.325
When will that be?

08:10.767 --> 08:11.882
Never.

08:17.567 --> 08:21.685
I can't. I just can't, I can't, I can't.
I can't possibly. I can't do it.

08:22.167 --> 08:26.001
It's too horrible.
Please, not another season, please.

08:26.087 --> 08:29.284
I beg you, don't make me do it.
Don't make me do it.

08:29.367 --> 08:30.720
- Don't make me do it.
- Everyone's ready for you, sir.

08:30.807 --> 08:34.515
Right, terrific. Okay, let's go!
Let's rock and roll, yeah?

08:35.567 --> 08:39.879
Good morning. Good morning, everyone.
Lovely to see you again.

08:40.207 --> 08:43.482
Or, rather, not see you.
Can we have the house lights, please?

08:43.847 --> 08:44.962
Now?

08:45.607 --> 08:46.722
Now?

08:47.607 --> 08:50.121
Not next Tuesday. Cheers. Boo!

08:50.207 --> 08:51.401
ALL: Boo!

08:51.607 --> 08:54.326
Here we are again. Here we are, yet again.

08:54.567 --> 08:58.401
Here we are, producing
the most popular show on television.

08:58.487 --> 09:02.275
The show to which not only America,
but now the whole world is glued. Yay!

09:05.487 --> 09:08.684
Which brings me to the task at hand.

09:08.767 --> 09:10.883
When you're on top,
there's only one place to go.

09:10.967 --> 09:12.844
- And where is that?
- Down!

09:13.167 --> 09:14.600
Who said that?

09:19.847 --> 09:21.997
"Down" is an incorrect answer.

09:23.727 --> 09:26.446
The answer is "up." Up!

09:28.047 --> 09:30.515
Because if you go down,
do you know what happens?

09:30.607 --> 09:34.919
All those people who were buttering you up
and smiling at you just moments ago

09:35.007 --> 09:38.283
leap on you and kick you and kick you

09:38.367 --> 09:41.916
and kick you and kick you
and kick you until you shut up.

09:46.127 --> 09:48.083
Down is not an option.

09:50.927 --> 09:51.962
So,

09:52.807 --> 09:56.117
let's go out there
and get some great contestants.

09:56.567 --> 09:59.445
And I don't just mean talented,
I mean human.

10:00.007 --> 10:04.159
And by human, I mean flawed.
And by flawed, I mean freaks.

10:04.367 --> 10:06.119
Bring me some freaks.

10:06.447 --> 10:08.756
Let's make this a show
that even I would watch.

10:09.647 --> 10:11.046
(DOORBELL RINGING)

10:11.327 --> 10:13.921
- Is it them? Is that them?
- Don't run!

10:14.327 --> 10:15.442
(THUDDING)

10:16.207 --> 10:18.038
Wait, wait, wait! Your hair!

10:18.767 --> 10:21.156
- Okay, okay, okay. Stop, Mom.
- All right. Go!

10:23.927 --> 10:25.804
Oh, Goddess, please, please, please.

10:32.207 --> 10:34.721
- Sally Kendoo?
- Yeah.

10:34.807 --> 10:36.525
We're from American Dreamz.

10:37.167 --> 10:39.522
- I know.
- And we're here to tell you...

10:39.607 --> 10:41.518
You've been selected
to perform on the show.

10:41.607 --> 10:42.676
(SCREAMING)

10:42.767 --> 10:43.995
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

10:44.087 --> 10:45.964
- Why do you do that?
- Do what?

10:46.047 --> 10:47.162
You know what.

10:47.247 --> 10:50.603
Just once I would like to tell when...
What are you doing?

10:51.247 --> 10:52.805
Sorry. Screaming.

10:53.167 --> 10:55.237
- Yes! Yes!
- Stop! Stop, stop screaming.

10:55.327 --> 10:56.680
- Stop.
- ITTLES: Dude.

10:56.807 --> 11:00.322
I'm really sorry.
We're gonna have to do this all over again.

11:00.407 --> 11:03.080
You're gonna have to go inside,
and come out

11:03.167 --> 11:04.964
and jump for joy all over again,

11:05.047 --> 11:07.436
because we didn't get it on camera.

11:08.367 --> 11:09.482
Okay.

11:10.767 --> 11:11.802
(DOOR CLOSES)

11:16.727 --> 11:18.718
Yes! I got it! I got it!

11:18.807 --> 11:20.763
- She's good.
- Yes! Yes!

11:22.887 --> 11:24.798
There's my guy.

11:25.127 --> 11:26.924
Congratulations, Mr President.

11:27.007 --> 11:30.238
You said we'd tear them a new one
and we tore them a new one.

11:30.567 --> 11:31.841
Excuse me.

11:31.927 --> 11:34.441
The big guy up there tore them a new one.
He smited them.

11:34.527 --> 11:36.597
- Smote.
- Smote, smited, whatever.

11:36.687 --> 11:38.484
What's with the papers? New puppy?

11:38.567 --> 11:40.478
- They're newspapers.
- I can see that.

11:40.567 --> 11:43.240
- Hi, Mrs P. You look beautiful.
- Good morning, Wally.

11:43.327 --> 11:46.637
- So, Mr P, you ready to meet the press?
- Not right now.

11:46.727 --> 11:48.604
Mr P, we discussed this.

11:48.687 --> 11:51.520
I mean, it was your idea
to meet the press after the big win.

11:51.607 --> 11:55.805
Herald in a new era of openness,
what with our overwhelming mandate.

11:55.967 --> 11:59.801
Yeah, I know.
It's just that there is a lot of stuff in here.

11:59.927 --> 12:02.646
It... There's a lot of interesting things.

12:02.727 --> 12:06.083
Well, yeah, there is a lot of stuff.
They have to fill the pages with something.

12:06.167 --> 12:08.522
But I think "interesting" is stretching it.

12:09.007 --> 12:11.282
Well, for instance, did you know

12:12.207 --> 12:15.404
that there are two kinds of Iraqistanis?

12:15.647 --> 12:17.478
(STAMMERING) I mean, actually,

12:17.567 --> 12:20.127
three kinds of Iraqis.

12:20.287 --> 12:22.642
Do you mean,
Sunnis and Shiites and Kurds?

12:23.207 --> 12:24.435
You knew about this?

12:24.527 --> 12:26.518
So did you. You knew this, Mr P.

12:26.607 --> 12:28.882
- Yeah, but...
- It's in your weekly digests.

12:28.967 --> 12:30.958
It's not like in this country,

12:31.047 --> 12:34.926
where whites and blacks and Latinos
all get along

12:35.007 --> 12:38.682
and there's no prejudicial deal
between them. I mean, these people,

12:38.767 --> 12:41.486
they have some long-standing
beefs with each other.

12:41.567 --> 12:45.276
MRS. STATON: Look, honey.
American Dreamz is coming on again soon.

12:46.487 --> 12:47.920
That's great. Great.

12:48.167 --> 12:51.876
Mr President,
we have to get you dressed and prepped.

12:51.967 --> 12:53.685
The press is waiting for you.

12:53.767 --> 12:55.997
You mean,
they're all out there waiting for me?

12:56.087 --> 12:57.486
They certainly are.

13:04.247 --> 13:06.807
Well, I just want to sit here
and read for a while.

13:06.887 --> 13:09.799
I think I deserve a break.
I'm kind of exhausted.

13:09.887 --> 13:11.286
Mr P, we need...

13:11.367 --> 13:14.598
I am not going out there right now,
g-damn it!

13:15.887 --> 13:19.243
Move it. Fun in a bucket.
Fun in a bucket, everybody.

13:19.327 --> 13:21.283
All right, all right.

13:21.647 --> 13:24.002
Hey, Willie, where's Sally?
Get her down here!

13:24.087 --> 13:25.600
- Oh, you know how girls are.
- Yeah.

13:25.687 --> 13:29.123
Hey, man. That's some girlfriend you got.
When you gonna marry that girl?

13:29.207 --> 13:30.606
We're talking about it, Uncle Fitz.

13:30.687 --> 13:32.359
We're thinking maybe next spring, huh?

13:32.447 --> 13:34.039
All righty. All right!

13:38.727 --> 13:40.524
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

13:40.847 --> 13:43.964
- WILLIE: Hey, Sally, it's you-know-who.
- Come on in, Willie.

13:44.687 --> 13:46.643
The door's locked, babe.

13:55.607 --> 13:57.199
What are you doing up here, Sally,

13:57.287 --> 14:00.006
when everybody's down there
celebrating your triumph?

14:00.087 --> 14:03.363
(CHUCKLING) Great.
I'm really excited for them.

14:03.727 --> 14:05.763
And they're really excited for you.

14:06.207 --> 14:09.802
You know, I am, too. I don't think
I've ever been prouder in my life.

14:09.887 --> 14:11.081
You know what?

14:11.167 --> 14:14.716
I was pretty excited for myself, too,
for like a half hour.

14:14.847 --> 14:18.920
And then it sunk in that this means nothing.

14:19.847 --> 14:21.200
Nothing?

14:21.407 --> 14:24.558
Sally, this is your dream.
You've always wanted to be on TV.

14:24.647 --> 14:27.605
No. I've always wanted to be a star.

14:27.767 --> 14:29.200
Isn't that the same thing?

14:29.287 --> 14:33.360
No, Willie, it's not the same thing.
Any idiot can be on TV nowadays.

14:33.647 --> 14:37.526
All you have to do is swap your wife
or eat a sheep's anus or something.

14:37.607 --> 14:40.804
Yes. Yes, but you are gonna sing.

14:41.647 --> 14:43.399
Yeah. I'm gonna sing.

14:44.087 --> 14:46.521
I'm gonna sing. And I'm not good enough.

14:46.647 --> 14:48.399
I'm not good enough!

14:48.687 --> 14:50.678
- Seven years!
- No, you know what I am?

14:50.767 --> 14:54.521
I am the best karaoke singer
in this county of Ohio.

14:54.607 --> 14:56.279
I'm going to go all the way out there, right?

14:56.367 --> 14:57.516
And I'm gonna come right back home

14:57.607 --> 14:59.962
and lose in the first round
because I'm just... I'm not good enough!

15:00.047 --> 15:01.082
- No way.
- Yes.

15:01.167 --> 15:02.202
- No way.
- Yes.

15:02.287 --> 15:05.245
No way, no way, no way. You're cute.

15:06.007 --> 15:07.804
You got a great voice.

15:07.887 --> 15:10.117
You got personality.

15:10.567 --> 15:12.956
And you got a great voice.

15:13.327 --> 15:16.603
Why, I think you're gonna win
the whole damn thing.

15:17.047 --> 15:20.835
And if for some reason those folks
have their heads up their stinkholes

15:20.927 --> 15:22.679
and you don't win, for whatever reason,

15:22.767 --> 15:24.678
I'm not gonna love you any less.

15:25.127 --> 15:27.800
I'm gonna love you more
because I see your real beauty

15:27.887 --> 15:30.720
and I don't need no TV show
to show it to me.

15:31.127 --> 15:34.324
Honey, I got some big news today, too.

15:39.407 --> 15:42.604
I'm being made assistant manager,
plumbing fixtures.

15:44.087 --> 15:45.725
Assistant manager.

15:46.287 --> 15:48.562
And you know what happens next.

15:48.727 --> 15:50.797
Manager, plumbing fixtures.

15:53.127 --> 15:54.355
Willie?

15:55.727 --> 15:57.877
I think it's time we broke up.

15:59.127 --> 16:00.196
What?

16:00.927 --> 16:04.397
It's just... I don't think it's working anymore.

16:04.487 --> 16:07.126
- Sure it is. It's going great.
- Not really.

16:07.207 --> 16:09.437
No, your life is here.

16:09.807 --> 16:11.479
And my life is...

16:12.247 --> 16:13.805
Or maybe it's...

16:14.207 --> 16:15.799
(IMITATES PLANE CRASHING)

16:16.207 --> 16:19.279
But either way, see, I can't take you with me.

16:21.687 --> 16:23.200
But I love you.

16:24.287 --> 16:26.801
I love you. Damn it, you can't do this to me.

16:26.887 --> 16:30.721
No, listen. You're the best thing
that's ever happened to me, I can't take it.

16:30.807 --> 16:32.798
You stay up here and cry.

16:33.767 --> 16:35.917
I'm going to go down and greet my fans.

16:36.087 --> 16:37.520
MAN: Sally!

16:37.607 --> 16:38.960
(ALL CHEERING)

16:40.367 --> 16:43.439
Hi, everyone!
Now, who'd like to hear a little song?

16:46.127 --> 16:47.276
MAN: Yeah!

16:48.167 --> 16:50.681
(UPBEAT INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

16:54.487 --> 16:57.285
(SINGING) She's a very freaky girl

16:57.727 --> 17:00.560
The kind you don't bring home to mama

17:01.367 --> 17:03.722
She's a super freak
Super freak

17:03.807 --> 17:06.162
She's super freaky

17:07.967 --> 17:09.241
(COUGHS)

17:10.166 --> 17:11.441
Wrong!

17:11.926 --> 17:13.519
Do you want this?

17:13.887 --> 17:15.115
Do you?

17:15.446 --> 17:17.358
Well, then get your ass in gear!

17:17.446 --> 17:19.517
- Lqbal, darling.
- What?

17:19.607 --> 17:22.246
Your cousin Omer is arriving any minute.

17:22.446 --> 17:25.644
Okay, I'll be up in a moment.
I'm doing something here.

17:25.727 --> 17:29.925
No, not in a moment.
A moment with you stretches into an hour.

17:30.007 --> 17:33.682
Your cousin has come halfway around
the world. Let's show him some hospitality.

17:33.767 --> 17:35.325
You come up right now!

17:35.407 --> 17:39.161
Don't get me upset today, okay?
You know I don't like to get upset.

17:50.007 --> 17:51.281
Nazneen!

17:51.607 --> 17:55.316
What a home. It is stupendous.

17:55.407 --> 17:57.682
What, this old place? Nazneen!

17:58.487 --> 17:59.761
Nazneen!

18:00.447 --> 18:02.358
- ALl: There you are.
- Aunt Nazneen.

18:02.447 --> 18:05.200
This young man thinks
our little home is stupendous.

18:05.327 --> 18:09.400
What, this old shack?
Let me see you. Let me see you.

18:09.687 --> 18:11.040
Hey, Omer!

18:11.287 --> 18:13.437
Could this be little Shabnum?

18:13.967 --> 18:15.878
Call me Shazzy. Everyone does.

18:15.967 --> 18:18.481
I'm so excited you're here.
It's been, what, 10 years, right?

18:18.567 --> 18:21.035
- Yes.
- We're gonna party like rock stars!

18:21.367 --> 18:22.436
Okay.

18:22.887 --> 18:24.479
Oh, Omer. Omer.

18:24.807 --> 18:28.595
I am so, so sorry about your mother.

18:29.247 --> 18:31.966
You know I loved her very, very much.

18:32.567 --> 18:35.684
I told her to leave Baghdad.
It's too dangerous.

18:37.567 --> 18:38.716
But she was headstrong.

18:38.807 --> 18:41.367
No, no, Nazneen.
This is a happy day. Remember.

18:41.447 --> 18:43.438
Oh, yes, of course, sweetie. Yes, honey.

18:43.527 --> 18:45.483
Hey, lqbal, this is your cousin, Omer!

18:45.567 --> 18:48.684
- Hello.
- Hi. Long time no see.

18:50.247 --> 18:52.602
Come on. Come on, everybody.
Come on, sweetheart.

18:52.687 --> 18:54.518
- Come on, let's be happy.
- Yes.

18:55.247 --> 18:58.956
The President hasn't made
a public appearance for the last three weeks.

18:59.327 --> 19:01.557
What about the rumours
that he has a mystery ailment?

19:01.647 --> 19:03.319
There is no mystery ailment.

19:03.407 --> 19:07.241
As we all know, the campaign process
takes a lot out of a person.

19:07.327 --> 19:11.286
And the President has been enjoying
the intervening time to rest and reflect.

19:11.367 --> 19:14.325
Is it true that he left President Putin on hold
for 30 minutes

19:14.407 --> 19:16.523
when the Russian president called
to congratulate him?

19:16.607 --> 19:17.926
Absolutely not.

19:18.007 --> 19:20.601
The President and Mr Putin had a nice talk.

19:20.687 --> 19:23.281
The President considers him a close friend,

19:23.407 --> 19:27.366
