36:22.167 --> 36:26.797
Because you'll be wearing this.

36:28.567 --> 36:30.000
What is that?

36:32.127 --> 36:34.482
Hey, Omer. Want to go to the mall?

36:35.207 --> 36:37.038
We just went last weekend.

36:37.127 --> 36:39.197
Yeah. Now we're going again.

36:39.367 --> 36:41.722
Why? Did you forget
to purchase something?

36:44.887 --> 36:48.402
If you do not mind,
I think I will pass on the mall today,

36:48.527 --> 36:51.246
I would like to just stay here and relax.

36:51.447 --> 36:54.007
- Okay. Bye!
- Bye.

37:11.927 --> 37:14.600
(MYSTICAL INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC
PLAYING)

37:16.607 --> 37:18.962
Thank you! Thank you! Thank you!

37:19.047 --> 37:23.325
You're too kind. You're too kind, really.
Thank you very much. Thank you.

37:23.407 --> 37:26.479
And now a piece from the classic,
Guys and Dolls.

37:29.087 --> 37:31.043
This is really a new low.

37:31.567 --> 37:34.320
- This lqbal guy can't sing.
- Neither can the Hasidic guy.

37:34.607 --> 37:36.563
What? The Hasidic guy rules.

37:36.647 --> 37:39.559
Wait! I hear singing.
Start the camera. Start the camera.

37:39.847 --> 37:42.884
(SINGING) Luck be a lady tonight

37:43.127 --> 37:46.324
Luck be a lady tonight, pah!

37:46.407 --> 37:49.683
Luck if you've ever been a lady to begin with

37:49.767 --> 37:52.281
Luck be a... tonight

37:55.087 --> 37:56.440
May I help you?

37:56.527 --> 38:00.839
You do not understand.
I have no desire to be on a television show.

38:01.127 --> 38:04.164
ITTLES: But you have real talent.
OMER: Do you really think so?

38:04.727 --> 38:08.276
But it is a moot point,
because it is not I you are looking for.

38:08.687 --> 38:10.359
It is my cousin, lqbal.

38:10.447 --> 38:12.756
I want him. No, I don't want him.

38:13.047 --> 38:14.878
I need him. I love him.

38:14.967 --> 38:17.686
That is it. That's my Arab.
Lqbal's out. Omer's in.

38:17.767 --> 38:19.359
Okay. We're working on it.

38:19.447 --> 38:22.962
Now here's a tape
that Sally Kendoo's agent sent over.

38:23.047 --> 38:25.117
She's the white-trash girl from Ohio.

38:25.207 --> 38:28.438
Apparently, she has a boyfriend
who was injured in the Iraq war,

38:28.527 --> 38:30.995
and this is footage of their reunion.

38:34.767 --> 38:36.758
Now look at this right here.

38:36.847 --> 38:38.439
Did you get that?

38:38.527 --> 38:39.721
Whoa.

38:40.407 --> 38:42.557
Give me that. Give me that. Give me that.

38:45.007 --> 38:46.645
Did you get that?

38:51.207 --> 38:52.481
Dirty bitch.

39:07.607 --> 39:09.837
Oh, my God. It's Martin Tweed!

39:10.007 --> 39:11.599
Martin Tweed, everyone!

39:11.687 --> 39:13.325
(WOMEN GASPING)

39:16.407 --> 39:17.442
ALL: Oh, my God!

39:17.527 --> 39:19.279
Get back. Get back, everyone!

39:19.887 --> 39:21.206
(DOOBELL RINGING)

39:33.847 --> 39:35.280
Mr Tweed.

39:36.007 --> 39:38.316
- Come on in.
- Thank you very much.

39:38.407 --> 39:40.238
- Mrs Kendoo?
- Oh, yes.

39:40.967 --> 39:42.685
And a lot of other Kendoos.

39:43.647 --> 39:47.401
Can I get you some hot bundt cake
or how about a beer?

39:47.487 --> 39:49.842
No, thank you very much.
I'm on a strict sashimi diet.

39:49.927 --> 39:52.839
Martin, Chet Krogl.
We met at upfronts a couple of years ago.

39:52.927 --> 39:54.201
Right. Yeah, Chet Krogl.

39:54.287 --> 39:56.801
- I don't want to talk to you.
- Okay. No problem.

39:56.887 --> 40:00.562
Do you know what? Do you think I might
go upstairs and talk to Sally in private?

40:01.087 --> 40:03.123
Oh, yeah, absolutely.

40:26.567 --> 40:29.286
- Cool car.
- Thank you very much. Thank you.

40:29.847 --> 40:32.759
Not easy renting a Ferrari in Padookie, Ohio.

40:35.727 --> 40:38.605
I'm surprised that you're here,
'cause I thought

40:38.687 --> 40:41.679
we were supposed to meet
for the first time onstage at the show.

40:41.767 --> 40:44.565
Yeah. Normally we would.
I never produce these segments.

40:44.647 --> 40:47.445
But I heard Padookie was an exciting town,
thought I'd check it out.

40:49.767 --> 40:51.803
- That was a joke.
- I'm aware.

40:52.567 --> 40:54.159
You didn't laugh.

40:54.327 --> 40:55.965
It wasn't funny.

40:57.527 --> 40:58.562
No.

41:00.247 --> 41:02.966
But why didn't you laugh
just to kiss my ass?

41:03.247 --> 41:05.238
I figure you didn't need me to kiss your ass.

41:05.327 --> 41:09.525
I mean, I'm sure you have people
kissing your ass 24 hours a day.

41:10.727 --> 41:15.084
And I guess, like, not kissing your ass
is like kissing your ass for most people.

41:16.287 --> 41:17.845
Absolutely right.

41:19.767 --> 41:23.077
It's weird. One can become quite detached
from reality when one's famous.

41:23.167 --> 41:24.316
Really.

41:25.767 --> 41:27.280
That sounds so cool.

41:27.367 --> 41:29.562
Yeah, it can be.

41:33.567 --> 41:37.446
So, Sally, I've seen your tapes
and I think you're very talented.

41:38.007 --> 41:40.965
- Really? You do?
- Well, moderately.

41:41.767 --> 41:43.439
But beyond that...

41:43.727 --> 41:45.080
Beyond that?

41:45.767 --> 41:47.519
I think I like you.

41:49.527 --> 41:51.279
I don't mean romantically, I mean

41:53.167 --> 41:55.556
I think I like you as a human being.

42:01.127 --> 42:02.924
MARTIN: So, have you ever been
in a Ferrari before?

42:03.007 --> 42:04.918
SALLY: Yeah, yeah, tons of times.

42:07.127 --> 42:10.244
You know, sometimes I'll be driving
my Enzo down Mulholland Drive,

42:10.327 --> 42:13.524
really gunning it. I'll look at the little railing
at the side of the road

42:13.607 --> 42:15.882
and the steep drop just beyond that
and I'll think,

42:15.967 --> 42:19.482
"Wouldn't it be great just to shoot
off the edge of the cliff?"

42:20.087 --> 42:22.806
- Wouldn't that be fun?
- Mr Tweed, I...

42:22.887 --> 42:25.720
No, no, no, no, no. Don't call me Mr Tweed.
Call me Tweedy.

42:25.807 --> 42:29.277
- Like Tweety Bird, but with a 'd'?
- Exactly, yeah.

42:30.007 --> 42:34.125
You know, my mum used to say to me,
"Martin, you have no talent.

42:34.247 --> 42:36.044
"No one will ever love you."

42:36.127 --> 42:39.517
Well, look at me now, Mum!
Look where no talent will get you!

42:39.807 --> 42:42.037
You jealous, drunk old bitch.

42:42.247 --> 42:43.965
Really, that's great.

42:44.047 --> 42:47.278
But, Tweedy, can you help me win?

42:47.527 --> 42:50.280
Because I would do absolutely anything
to win this show.

42:50.367 --> 42:53.518
I'd love to help you, Sally,
but there's only so much I can do.

42:53.607 --> 42:56.075
It's down to you.
You've got to make the people love you.

42:56.167 --> 42:59.364
- The way that they love you?
- Nope. Nobody loves me.

43:00.167 --> 43:03.557
My mum was right about that.
But it's fine, I don't care.

43:04.007 --> 43:07.238
I don't want the fake bullshit
that passes for love in this world.

43:07.327 --> 43:11.081
Well, you don't have to worry about me,
I'm not even sure that I like you.

43:11.607 --> 43:12.642
Wow.

43:13.207 --> 43:15.118
My God,
I can't believe I just said that out loud.

43:15.207 --> 43:16.879
I never say stuff like that out loud.

43:16.967 --> 43:19.162
I think you are a rapacious little bitch.

43:19.247 --> 43:21.920
Well, I think you're a self-involved,
preening idiot.

43:22.007 --> 43:24.805
Sociopathic, egomaniacal,
Madonna wannabe.

43:24.887 --> 43:28.880
No-talent, famous-for-being-famous,
third-rate, Regis Philbin clone!

43:31.127 --> 43:33.687
SHAZZY: So, at the mall today,
I upgraded my plan to 5,000 minutes,

43:33.767 --> 43:34.836
but it's a family plan.

43:34.927 --> 43:37.964
- Thank you, Auntie.
- IQBAL: You should've gotten 10,000.

43:38.047 --> 43:39.765
- Lqbal?
- Yeah.

43:40.567 --> 43:44.003
Something very odd happened today.
It's funny, really.

43:44.087 --> 43:47.841
You see, these people from the
American Dreamz television show came by.

43:51.047 --> 43:53.197
- Yeah?
- And...

43:55.687 --> 43:57.723
- And?
- And I was using your stage

43:57.807 --> 44:00.321
and they heard me singing
and they want me to be on the show.

44:03.127 --> 44:07.439
I'm sorry. Did you say they want you
to sing on the show?

44:07.527 --> 44:08.562
Mmm-hmm.

44:08.647 --> 44:09.921
Isn't that amusing?

44:10.007 --> 44:11.759
- Holy crap.
- NAZNEEN: Shazzy.

44:12.247 --> 44:14.556
- Congratulations, Omer!
- Thank you.

44:14.647 --> 44:16.797
"Congratulations, Omer!"
That's what you have to say!

44:16.887 --> 44:18.605
"Congratulations, Omer!"

44:18.967 --> 44:21.686
Do you know how hard I have worked
to get on this show?

44:21.767 --> 44:23.519
You've stolen my dream!

44:23.607 --> 44:26.997
I'm so sorry. I told them.
I told them they had made a mistake.

44:27.407 --> 44:28.476
But do not worry.

44:28.567 --> 44:32.560
I will simply refuse
to be on the television show. Yes?

44:32.647 --> 44:35.002
Yes, and then they must take you instead.

44:35.127 --> 44:36.845
They don't want me.

44:37.527 --> 44:40.121
Nobody wants me!

44:40.527 --> 44:43.246
Nonsense, sweetheart. We all love you.

44:44.407 --> 44:47.524
Is that going to make me famous?
I don't think so.

44:56.527 --> 44:59.439
MARTIN: (ON TV) Next week, the exciting
premiere episode of American Dreamz.

44:59.527 --> 45:02.678
Which of these hopefuls will live
the next American dream?

45:07.967 --> 45:10.879
Wait. Rewind the TiVo.

45:16.327 --> 45:17.601
Pause it.

45:20.927 --> 45:23.282
- Hello.
- Hello, Mrs Riza.

45:23.687 --> 45:26.520
- Is Omer at home, please?
- Yes, he is.

45:27.287 --> 45:29.642
Who shall I say is asking for him?

45:29.727 --> 45:32.036
Just some friends.

45:34.287 --> 45:35.879
NAZNEEN: Come in, please.

45:42.567 --> 45:45.684
- Sun block, anyone?
- Yes. Thank you, Auntie.

45:45.767 --> 45:46.802
NAZNEEN: Sure.

45:47.327 --> 45:50.364
Now, I am going to bring you boys
a little treat.

45:50.807 --> 45:52.081
Thank you.

45:59.367 --> 46:01.756
Very cushy situation you have here.

46:03.527 --> 46:06.564
- No pool?
- No. No, just the Jacuzzi.

46:11.447 --> 46:15.076
The Western Command has learned of you
being chosen to sing and dance

46:15.167 --> 46:19.285
on a hedonistic television show
aptly named American Dreamz.

46:20.447 --> 46:23.484
Wow. You guys heard about that?

46:25.807 --> 46:27.604
OMER: It's all a big mistake, you see.

46:27.687 --> 46:30.485
They got me mixed up with my cousin.

46:30.927 --> 46:34.636
Because I would never engage
in such a frivolous activity.

46:35.207 --> 46:38.517
In fact, I'm going to tell them
I will not be on the show.

46:38.647 --> 46:40.717
You are to do no such thing.

46:40.967 --> 46:42.958
You are to perform on the show.

46:43.047 --> 46:45.481
And you must get
to the championship round,

46:45.567 --> 46:47.683
because judging the championship round

46:47.767 --> 46:51.840
will be none other than the
President of the United States of America.

46:52.727 --> 46:54.160
The President?

46:54.447 --> 46:59.123
When you are onstage with the President,
you will have smuggled in an explosive belt.

46:59.407 --> 47:01.682
And you are to martyr yourself.

47:01.767 --> 47:04.839
Killing, in the process,
the head of the serpent.

47:05.807 --> 47:08.241
What if I don't make it to the final round?

47:08.327 --> 47:11.285
Omer, folks don't call me "The Torturer"

47:11.367 --> 47:13.403
because I don't like to torture people.

47:13.487 --> 47:15.205
You know what I mean?

47:17.487 --> 47:20.797
Now, who would like to try
some grapefruit sorbet?

47:24.487 --> 47:28.241
In a busy political week capped by
a marked increase in his approval ratings,

47:28.327 --> 47:32.081
the President has stepped back into the
public eye in a string of high-profile events.

47:32.167 --> 47:34.840
REPORTER: (ON TV) Earlier this week,
he hosted the Ukrainian President,

47:34.927 --> 47:38.044
lifted weights with the head
of the Organisation of African States,

47:38.127 --> 47:40.118
spent some time with his dog, Henry,

47:40.207 --> 47:43.438
and chatted with Carmen Electra
at a black-tie event.

47:43.527 --> 47:44.880
- Thank you.
- You come back now, all right?

47:44.967 --> 47:46.480
- Okay. Nice meeting you.
- Okay.

47:48.247 --> 47:51.637
After weeks of seclusion,
suddenly the President is everywhere.

47:51.727 --> 47:53.046
Even signing on to guest judge

47:53.127 --> 47:56.483
the finale of the top-rated television show,
American Dreamz.

47:56.567 --> 47:58.797
You hear that? We're back.

47:59.767 --> 48:01.564
All right. Now hold still.

48:04.207 --> 48:05.356
It tickles.

48:05.447 --> 48:08.086
You want to wear this thing all night?
Then sit still.

48:12.167 --> 48:15.477
This thing is incredible. Great reception.

48:17.007 --> 48:19.885
I can't believe I didn't think of it earlier.

48:20.247 --> 48:23.922
Hell of a week, sir!
You really got back on message.

48:24.007 --> 48:26.567
That's because you're telling me
what the message is.

48:26.647 --> 48:27.796
Exactly.

48:28.927 --> 48:31.805
I just love that Carmen Electra. Thanks.

48:32.367 --> 48:34.562
I would have never had the courage to go up

48:34.647 --> 48:37.241
and talk to her by myself, face to face.

48:38.007 --> 48:39.440
Engaging girl.

48:40.487 --> 48:42.557
Good night, Mr President.

48:44.687 --> 48:46.086
(DOOR CLOSING)

48:53.287 --> 48:56.006
One and two. Three and four.

48:56.167 --> 48:57.282
Five...

48:58.167 --> 48:59.202
Hey.

48:59.927 --> 49:01.121
What are you doing?

49:01.207 --> 49:04.279
Nothing. Nothing.
I'm just rehearsing some dance steps.

49:04.367 --> 49:05.402
Oh.

49:05.607 --> 49:07.040
Look, lqbal.

49:08.007 --> 49:09.884
- I am so sorry...
- Stop.

49:11.447 --> 49:14.803
I don't want your pity.
Does it look like I need pity?

49:15.687 --> 49:18.201
No, no, no. You have far too much dignity.

49:18.287 --> 49:22.075
If these people know nothing about talent,
there's not much I can do about it, is there?

49:25.047 --> 49:27.845
So let's see it. Let's see your dance steps.

49:29.487 --> 49:30.761
All right.

49:34.127 --> 49:36.960
One and two. Three and four.

49:37.287 --> 49:38.356
What?

49:38.447 --> 49:40.677
Oh, there's no way
you're gonna win this thing.

49:41.327 --> 49:43.238
I know. I fear as much.

49:49.967 --> 49:52.162
IQBAL: Get up there. Up on the stage.

49:52.447 --> 49:53.880
Are you sure?

49:53.967 --> 49:56.162
Do it. Before I change my mind.

49:58.047 --> 50:01.722
Okay. Now this is just the bass track.
It's good to practice moves to.

50:02.007 --> 50:05.920
- I don't like this kind of music.
- It's just a bass track. It's just for rehearsal!

50:07.487 --> 50:08.681
Okay.

50:10.727 --> 50:14.766
Now, one problem you have is you move
like a re-animated corpse in a zombie movie.

50:14.847 --> 50:16.041
Not good.

50:16.287 --> 50:17.800
You need to loosen up.

50:18.807 --> 50:20.798
Okay. Come on, let's go.

50:20.887 --> 50:22.764
Free-form jazz dancing,
right now, immediately.

50:22.847 --> 50:24.963
Lqbal, why are you helping me?

50:25.527 --> 50:27.358
I destroyed your dream.

50:28.407 --> 50:29.522
Yeah.

50:30.087 --> 50:31.315
You did.

50:31.847 --> 50:33.565
But that was yesterday.

50:33.967 --> 50:37.277
Today, I've turned a page
on a new chapter in my life.

50:37.367 --> 50:41.121
I'm not sure being a performer
was ever what I was really meant for.

50:41.207 --> 50:44.563
I'm more of a behind-the-scenes player.
A puppeteer.

50:44.767 --> 50:46.405
A Svengali, if you will.

50:47.927 --> 50:49.406
As of today,

50:50.207 --> 50:51.845
I'm your manager.

50:53.047 --> 50:57.438
This is Martin Tweed, and I am
in the small town of Padookie, Ohio.

50:58.007 --> 51:00.441
Our first dream starts right here,

51:00.527 --> 51:04.406
where local chanteuse Sally Kendoo
hopes her dream comes true.

51:04.687 --> 51:06.120
(SCREAMING)

51:06.207 --> 51:08.004
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

51:08.327 --> 51:12.764
It was always Sally's idea to perform,
not mine.

51:13.327 --> 51:16.524
I mean, she's been wanting to do this
since she was six months old.

51:17.127 --> 51:18.401
Sing!

51:19.767 --> 51:23.362
She did it before. She's just shy.
Come on, honey. Sing!

51:23.807 --> 51:25.718
MARTIN: The last remaining business
on Main Street

51:25.807 --> 51:27.525
is Harry's Hangdown Bar and Grill

51:27.767 --> 51:30.235
where Sally works as a part-time waitress.

51:30.327 --> 51:32.158
The Hangdown is a home away from home

51:32.247 --> 51:34.886
for the largely unemployed male population
of Padookie.

51:34.967 --> 51:36.036
(ALL CHEERING)

51:40.007 --> 51:41.520
MAN: Come on! Yeah!

51:42.007 --> 51:44.965
MARTIN: Sally's high-school sweetheart
is a decorated war veteran,

51:45.047 --> 51:46.685
a real American hero.

51:48.407 --> 51:52.241
And halfway across America,
hailing from halfway around the world,

51:52.327 --> 51:55.603
Omer Obeidi lives with his cousins,
the Riza Family.

51:55.687 --> 51:58.247
A refugee from the mayhem
of the Middle East.

51:58.327 --> 52:01.956
I cannot believe my good fortune
to be competing on the show.

52:02.887 --> 52:05.606
This is truly an American dream come true.

52:06.727 --> 52:07.842
(WHISPERING) Now.

52:08.207 --> 52:09.356
Now.

52:09.487 --> 52:12.320
America, you will be Omerised.

52:14.287 --> 52:17.757
MARTIN: Like any American kid,
Omer likes to hang out at the mall

52:17.847 --> 52:19.485
where his posse all know him.

52:19.567 --> 52:21.285
Omer, American Dreamz, baby!

52:21.367 --> 52:23.358
Yo, Big O!
I like your style.

52:23.447 --> 52:25.961
O-mizzer! That's my dawg right there!

52:26.047 --> 52:27.844
Keep it real, man! Remember that.
Keep it real.

52:27.927 --> 52:31.966
There may not be peace in the Middle East,
but there is Middle East in this piece,

52:32.047 --> 52:36.438
as we visit cantor Sholem Glickstein,
recent Israeli immigrant.

52:36.687 --> 52:38.040
I wish Omer luck.

52:38.247 --> 52:41.319
I wish all of the contestants luck,
because I'm coming for them.

52:41.407 --> 52:42.476
Do you hear that?

52:42.567 --> 52:45.843
Do you hear that? I am coming
for you, bitches! I am coming for you!

52:46.927 --> 52:48.155
Looks great.

52:48.287 --> 52:51.006
Big day tomorrow, boss. You fired up?

52:51.647 --> 52:54.639
Yes. I am fired up.

52:58.567 --> 53:00.125
- Debra?
- Yes.

53:00.967 --> 53:02.639
Do you think I'm lovable?

53:03.687 --> 53:04.881
Lovable?

53:05.127 --> 53:08.403
Yeah. Yes, sure, very.

53:09.887 --> 53:11.161
Frank?

53:12.647 --> 53:15.559
I love you. That's all I know.

53:19.247 --> 53:21.158
Okay, thanks. You can go.

53:43.487 --> 53:46.718
Welcome! Welcome!
Welcome back, America!

53:47.207 --> 53:48.799
- Boo!
- AUDIENCE: Boo!

53:49.567 --> 53:51.842
I'm Martin Tweed
and I am so delighted to be back

53:51.927 --> 53:53.883
with another exciting season
of American Dreamz.

53:53.967 --> 53:55.400
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

53:55.767 --> 53:59.316
We have some amazing dreamers
who are gonna perform for you tonight.

53:59.527 --> 54:02.087
Some will triumph.
Some will sink back into obscurity.

54:02.167 --> 54:04.840
Only one will become
America's newest sensation.

54:04.927 --> 54:06.076
It's up to you, America.

54:06.167 --> 54:08.886
Only you have the awesome power
to lift someone up into the heavens

54:08.967 --> 54:10.241
and create a new star.

54:10.327 --> 54:12.397
And here are your dreamers!

54:22.607 --> 54:25.360
Let's go! Let's go! Let's go!
Come on, watch your step! Watch your step!

54:25.447 --> 54:28.200
Go, go, go, go! Come on, get on up there!

54:28.287 --> 54:30.801
Let's go! Go! Move it out! Move it!

54:53.647 --> 54:56.957
I'd like to dedicate this song
to a real American hero.

54:57.167 --> 54:59.727
My boyfriend, William Williams.

55:03.167 --> 55:07.524
He risked his life for our freedom,
and that's a real American dream.

55:13.127 --> 55:15.402
(SINGING) Mommy, don't drink

55:15.487 --> 55:18.843
Me to bed tonight

55:19.527 --> 55:22.564
What's gotten into

55:22.647 --> 55:25.161
Your head tonight?

55:25.527 --> 55:28.041
Did I make you mad?

55:28.767 --> 55:31.361
Is that why you're sad?

55:32.447 --> 55:34.881
And, Daddy, where have

55:35.167 --> 55:38.125
You been all my life?

55:38.807 --> 55:41.321
Mommy said that

55:41.567 --> 55:44.286
You got a new wife

55:44.487 --> 55:47.638
And there's nothing to do

55:47.887 --> 55:50.606
But I know that's not true

55:50.887 --> 55:54.243
And there's no one to hold me

55:54.727 --> 55:57.287
Close when I cry

55:57.847 --> 56:00.645
To rock me so gentle

56:00.847 --> 56:03.725
Till the storm passes by

56:04.687 --> 56:07.076
And I'm just a kid

56:07.367 --> 56:10.564
But I know it ain't right

56:12.127 --> 56:14.880
So, Mommy, don't drink

56:14.967 --> 56:18.880
Me to bed tonight

56:33.407 --> 56:34.681
Sally.

56:37.207 --> 56:38.959
I think you're terrific.

56:39.087 --> 56:42.966
In fact, I think you have star quality.

56:43.647 --> 56:45.365
Thank you, Mr Tweed.

56:48.087 --> 56:49.725
Sally Kendoo.

56:53.287 --> 56:56.006
(SINGING) Girl, let's not be friends

56:56.087 --> 56:57.964
'Cause we've shared too much

56:58.047 --> 57:02.757
Girl, you know that
I'm yearning for your touch

57:02.927 --> 57:07.125
'Cause I can't be less than your everything

57:07.367 --> 57:09.756
'Cause I'll lay down and cry

57:09.847 --> 57:12.077
I'll curl up and die

57:12.167 --> 57:16.638
Don't let this be how my story ends

57:16.727 --> 57:18.957
It's love or good-bye

57:19.047 --> 57:21.561
So let's not be friends

57:21.647 --> 57:24.207
(SINGING) I'm a rocking man

57:24.287 --> 57:27.199
I'm a genuine rocking man

57:27.287 --> 57:31.326
I'm a rock, rock, rock, rock, rock
Rocking man!

57:32.967 --> 57:36.437
I'm a rock, rock, rock, rock, rock, rock, rock

57:36.527 --> 57:38.483
(SINGING) I never felt

57:38.887 --> 57:41.526
This way

57:42.287 --> 57:46.724
Before

57:48.207 --> 57:52.246
(SINGING) Girl, you know I want you
I got a rocket launcher

57:52.327 --> 57:55.046
So, baby, let's get raunchy tonight

57:55.127 --> 57:57.038
CHORUS: Let's get raunchy tonight

57:57.127 --> 58:00.802
I don't want to taunt you
Or take you out and flaunt you

58:00.887 --> 58:03.447
So, baby, let's get raunchy, all right

58:03.527 --> 58:06.166
CHORUS: Let's get raunchy, baby

58:14.847 --> 58:16.166
Sholem.

58:16.807 --> 58:18.877
I only have two words for you.

58:18.967 --> 58:20.161
Mazel tov!

58:20.847 --> 58:23.315
No, you were wonderful. Really, wonderful.

58:24.727 --> 58:27.685
Good news, Pauly.
I don't want to be your friend.

58:27.767 --> 58:30.725
In fact, you make me
want to projectile vomit.

58:31.407 --> 58:36.083
Bobby, I think my ears are actually bleeding.
You are like a musical Ebola virus.

58:36.407 --> 58:37.681
Cindy.

58:38.967 --> 58:41.276
I'm afraid I have felt this way before.

58:41.367 --> 58:44.916
And it was just before I tried to kill myself.
Sorry, love.

58:46.967 --> 58:48.116
Sorry.

58:50.647 --> 58:52.046
I hate you!

58:52.847 --> 58:54.280
Nice girl. Cindy.

59:04.607 --> 59:05.881
Here he is.

59:08.087 --> 59:09.839
Fantastic, Omer.

59:16.047 --> 59:18.436
- Don't clap.
- No, no, of course.

59:22.807 --> 59:24.365
(SINGING) To dream

59:24.647 --> 59:27.286
The impossible dream

59:29.887 --> 59:32.242
To fight

59:32.327 --> 59:36.161
The unbeatable foe

59:37.487 --> 59:39.637
To bear

59:39.967 --> 59:43.482
With unbearable sorrow

59:45.087 --> 59:48.682
To run where the brave dare not go

59:48.767 --> 59:51.998
What the hell is that?
He looks like he stepped on a scorpion.

59:52.087 --> 59:54.555
This is my quest

59:54.647 --> 59:57.559
To follow that star

59:57.647 --> 01:00:00.320
No matter how hopeless

01:00:00.407 --> 01:00:03.160
No matter how far

01:00:03.247 --> 01:00:05.556
To fight for the right

01:00:05.967 --> 01:00:08.845
Without question or pause

01:00:08.927 --> 01:00:12.044
To be willing to march into hell

01:00:12.127 --> 01:00:15.483
For a heavenly cause

01:00:15.567 --> 01:00:17.797
Go, Omer. Go.

01:00:17.887 --> 01:00:22.165
To reach the unreachable star

01:00:24.207 --> 01:00:26.243
You have been Omerised! Pah!

01:00:39.647 --> 01:00:40.762
Omer,

01:00:41.567 --> 01:00:43.398
that was strange.

01:00:43.807 --> 01:00:45.160
Strange,

01:00:46.487 --> 01:00:47.966
but rather wonderful.

01:00:48.767 --> 01:00:50.723
I think I have been Omerised.

01:00:50.807 --> 01:00:52.763
I think I might be Omer-sexual.

01:01:16.967 --> 01:01:18.320
Oh, my God!

01:01:21.087 --> 01:01:22.202
Yes!

01:01:22.727 --> 01:01:24.957
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

01:01:25.047 --> 01:01:26.241
Yes!

01:01:49.527 --> 01:01:53.679
SALLY: (SINGING) They came on boats
From across the sea

01:01:55.447 --> 01:01:57.756
From faraway places

01:01:57.847 --> 01:02:00.680
And far distant lands

01:02:01.887 --> 01:02:03.798
And still they come

01:02:04.127 --> 01:02:07.483
To a place where they're free

01:02:08.327 --> 01:02:10.318
They fly in on planes

01:02:10.487 --> 01:02:13.559
With hope in their hands

01:02:14.087 --> 01:02:16.601
Sometimes it feels

01:02:16.887 --> 01:02:19.685
Like we're stuffed to the seams

01:02:20.127 --> 01:02:24.279
But it's everyone's God-given right

01:02:25.767 --> 01:02:28.884
To follow their dreams

01:02:28.967 --> 01:02:31.037
CHORUS: My American dream

01:02:31.967 --> 01:02:34.720
SALLY: Will come true for me

01:02:35.127 --> 01:02:36.765
CHORUS: My American dream

01:02:36.887 --> 01:02:40.562
SALLY: For all to see

01:02:41.887 --> 01:02:44.879
Every woman and man

01:02:45.487 --> 01:02:48.718
Has their own destiny

01:02:49.527 --> 01:02:53.440
To dream American Dreamz

01:02:53.727 --> 01:02:55.843
Dreamz with a Z

01:02:55.927 --> 01:03:00.284
To dream American Dreamz

01:03:00.367 --> 01:03:03.040
Dreamz with a Z

01:03:04.247 --> 01:03:06.681
We began the show with 50 dreamers.

01:03:07.247 --> 01:03:09.397
Now we're down to just three.

01:03:12.447 --> 01:03:13.766
- Boo.
- AUDIENCE: Boo!

01:03:14.687 --> 01:03:16.166
How are you doing?

01:03:16.887 --> 01:03:18.366
You all right?

01:03:19.727 --> 01:03:21.877
And the two finalists

01:03:29.367 --> 01:03:32.882
will be revealed after this commercial break
brought to you by American Motors,

01:03:32.967 --> 01:03:36.562
introducing "The Tank," 50%% larger
than the next biggest SUV on the road,

01:03:36.647 --> 01:03:38.046
because you need it.

01:03:38.487 --> 01:03:41.638
STAGE MANAGER: And we're out! Come on,
people. Hair and makeup, let's go, let's go.

01:03:42.727 --> 01:03:45.036
All right.
Give me some room over here, Travis.

01:03:45.127 --> 01:03:48.722
Calm, calm, calm, calm.
Thank you, thank you very much.

01:03:49.047 --> 01:03:51.607
Here you go.
And you're supposed to be drinking this.

01:03:51.687 --> 01:03:53.723
- Must I?
- Contractually, yes.

01:03:53.807 --> 01:03:56.002
- Your envelope.
- Thank you.

01:03:57.167 --> 01:03:59.158
STAGE MANAGER: All right, let's wrap it up.
Let's get it started.

01:03:59.247 --> 01:04:00.441
Let's get the chairs out, let's go.

01:04:00.527 --> 01:04:02.358
Get the lead out. Big smiles, everyone.

01:04:02.447 --> 01:04:05.644
Big smiles. And we're back. Three, two.

01:04:06.847 --> 01:04:09.725
Excuse me. Delicious.
That's wildly refreshing.

01:04:10.527 --> 01:04:14.156
And now, America, you have voted.

01:04:25.287 --> 01:04:26.959
- Sholem Glickstein?
- Yeah.

01:04:38.447 --> 01:04:39.721
You are

01:04:42.127 --> 01:04:44.004
not a winner.

01:04:48.967 --> 01:04:51.640
This week's winners who will move on
to the championship round

01:04:51.727 --> 01:04:54.446
are Sally Kendoo and Omer Obeidi.
And don't forget,

01:04:54.527 --> 01:04:57.439
on next week's finale, special guest judge,
the President.

01:05:05.647 --> 01:05:06.762
Honey?

01:05:07.967 --> 01:05:10.003
I have a confession to make.

01:05:12.407 --> 01:05:14.682
I haven't been taking my happy pills.

01:05:16.367 --> 01:05:19.165
Actually, I haven't been taking mine, either.

01:05:19.487 --> 01:05:22.604
- But you don't seem sad.
- Well, I guess I'm not.

01:05:23.327 --> 01:05:26.876
At first, those happy pills
really helped me a lot.

01:05:27.167 --> 01:05:31.604
But, eventually, I think they were just
kind of like placebos.

01:05:32.207 --> 01:05:35.119
Placebos? Aren't they illegal?

01:05:36.607 --> 01:05:40.885
No, Poopie. It means fake.

01:05:43.887 --> 01:05:45.240
Well, yeah.

01:05:45.487 --> 01:05:46.602
Well.

01:05:49.807 --> 01:05:51.035
You know,

01:05:52.047 --> 01:05:55.596
I guess I kind of feel like I'm a placebo.

01:05:58.607 --> 01:06:01.519
I mean, I've had speech writers

01:06:01.927 --> 01:06:03.963
writing for me all my career,

01:06:04.047 --> 01:06:07.005
and advisors telling me
what positions to take.

01:06:09.127 --> 01:06:12.802
I can't even remember why I wanted
to get into politics to begin with.

01:06:14.367 --> 01:06:17.086
I think it's 'cause my mom wanted me to.

01:06:18.087 --> 01:06:20.521
Show my dad any idiot could do it.

01:06:21.607 --> 01:06:25.361
Maybe I ought to just chuck the whole thing.
What do you think?

01:06:25.567 --> 01:06:27.842
Starting with that American Dreamz deal.

01:06:27.927 --> 01:06:29.997
Don't you say that.

01:06:31.327 --> 01:06:35.320
Do you remember what I said
the first time I met you?

01:06:36.127 --> 01:06:37.242
Yeah.

01:06:37.487 --> 01:06:40.445
"Hey, jerk-off, you spilled your beer on me."

01:06:41.687 --> 01:06:43.166
After that.

01:06:43.887 --> 01:06:46.037
When you went and got that towel

01:06:46.127 --> 01:06:49.881
and borrowed that T-shirt
from one of your frat brothers for me.

01:06:50.687 --> 01:06:53.360
I said, "Now that there is a good guy."

01:06:53.767 --> 01:06:55.803
And I still think so today.

01:06:57.007 --> 01:07:01.159
So you just go on and be on that show.

01:07:02.327 --> 01:07:06.639
And then, afterwards, we will tell Wally
no more earplugs, okay?

01:07:08.767 --> 01:07:11.327
Well, how am I gonna know what to say?

01:07:12.767 --> 01:07:15.235
Well, we will think of it together.

01:07:17.887 --> 01:07:19.400
Mmm-hmm.

01:07:25.407 --> 01:07:27.318
Look at this! "Omer Mania!"

01:07:27.647 --> 01:07:30.366
"America's newest mascot, adorable,

01:07:30.847 --> 01:07:33.884
"Omer Obeidi
has 'Omerised' the whole country."

01:07:34.407 --> 01:07:36.284
It should have been me.

01:07:37.247 --> 01:07:39.841
I mean, great, Omer! They love you!

01:07:39.927 --> 01:07:40.962
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

01:07:41.047 --> 01:07:42.275
AGHA: Room service.

01:07:43.767 --> 01:07:47.157
Hey, what are you gonna say
when you meet the President?

01:07:48.367 --> 01:07:49.402
Sorry?

01:07:49.487 --> 01:07:52.047
"Sorry?" Omer, you crack me up.

01:07:52.127 --> 01:07:54.846
Okay, we got two orders
spicy tuna hand rolls,

01:07:54.927 --> 01:07:57.760
a plate of fresh fruit
and some chimichangas.

01:08:04.807 --> 01:08:07.367
Oh, you guys go ahead and start eating. I...

01:08:07.447 --> 01:08:10.996
I have to go talk to the waiter in private
for a moment.

01:08:13.207 --> 01:08:14.322
So.

01:08:15.447 --> 01:08:18.200
You have become quite the famous man.

01:08:19.006 --> 01:08:22.397
- You know why they vote for you?
- Because they like me?

01:08:22.487 --> 01:08:23.636
(SCOFFS)

01:08:24.687 --> 01:08:27.281
Because you are a figure of fun to them.

01:08:27.966 --> 01:08:31.163
They see you prancing and singing
and they can forget the terrors

01:08:31.247 --> 01:08:34.921
they've inflicted on our lands
with their soldiers and weapons.

01:08:35.006 --> 01:08:36.962
It could be. Yes, I guess.

01:08:37.207 --> 01:08:39.004
But I have to hand it to you.

01:08:39.167 --> 01:08:43.365
You have put us in a wonderful position
to strike them a crippling blow.

01:08:46.447 --> 01:08:48.358
About that crippling blow.

01:08:48.966 --> 01:08:50.639
I really don't know
how I'm supposed to do it.

01:08:50.727 --> 01:08:53.116
You see, really,
there is a lot of security there.

01:08:53.207 --> 01:08:56.165
All you have to do is get me and the rest
of your brothers on the guest list

01:08:56.247 --> 01:08:58.044
for the studio audience.

01:08:58.247 --> 01:09:01.876
We will smuggle in the explosive device
in pieces, assemble it there,

01:09:01.966 --> 01:09:03.639
and then you must only retrieve it

01:09:03.727 --> 01:09:07.162
in the toilet-seat-cover dispenser
in the men's bathroom.

01:09:07.367 --> 01:09:10.165
Then, when you meet the President

01:09:10.487 --> 01:09:13.285
and shake his hand, live on television,

01:09:13.367 --> 01:09:15.403
you will ignite the device.

01:09:16.006 --> 01:09:18.362
And I will see you in paradise.

01:09:19.607 --> 01:09:21.484
You will be killed, too?

01:09:21.767 --> 01:09:24.679
Not yet. It's a pretty small bomb.

01:09:25.247 --> 01:09:27.807
But I'll see you up there
in a few years, I'm sure.

01:09:30.846 --> 01:09:34.999
So, I'm just curious.
How is this Martin Tweed in person?

01:09:37.447 --> 01:09:38.720
(DOOR OPENS)

01:09:38.926 --> 01:09:41.202
Sally, Sally, Sally. I am so proud of you.

01:09:41.287 --> 01:09:44.323
I always knew you had a great voice
and now the whole world knows it, too.

01:09:44.407 --> 01:09:48.604
William, no, no. I have not won yet.
Everybody seems to be forgetting that.

01:09:48.687 --> 01:09:51.997
You know, folks,
they love that Middle Eastern guy.

01:09:52.087 --> 01:09:53.725
They love you more.

01:09:53.966 --> 01:09:57.642
They love us more. You know how many hits
we got on our website last night?

01:09:57.727 --> 01:09:59.319
Sixteen million.

01:10:00.127 --> 01:10:02.197
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

01:10:03.047 --> 01:10:07.677
God, William. You make me feel bad.
Why do you care so much about me?

01:10:07.847 --> 01:10:09.121
Why?

01:10:10.167 --> 01:10:14.046
Because, honey, you are my dream girl.

01:10:14.247 --> 01:10:15.600
Yuck.

01:10:15.687 --> 01:10:17.803
I can't stand looking
at those damn French fries anymore.

01:10:17.887 --> 01:10:19.479
Just cover them up or something.

01:10:20.127 --> 01:10:22.038
Sally Kendoo, I love you.

01:10:22.127 --> 01:10:24.357
Okay? I love you.

01:10:24.607 --> 01:10:27.121
I love how you binge eat
and then starve yourself.

01:10:27.207 --> 01:10:29.323
I love how pretty you sing,
whether it's in the shower

01:10:29.407 --> 01:10:31.443
or in front of millions of TV viewers.

01:10:31.527 --> 01:10:35.839
I look at you and I see that same girl
that I fell in love with in high school.

01:10:36.567 --> 01:10:39.240
And I'd like to know, right here and now,

01:10:40.007 --> 01:10:44.159
if you'd help to make my dream come true
and marry me?

01:10:45.367 --> 01:10:46.686
Oh, my God.

01:10:48.287 --> 01:10:49.686
Oh, my Lord.

01:10:49.767 --> 01:10:51.962
Hold it right there! Nobody move.

01:10:52.047 --> 01:10:54.038
- Chet, what are you doing?
- I'm calling the camera crew.

01:10:54.127 --> 01:10:56.083
No, you're not. Put the phone down, Chet.

01:10:56.167 --> 01:10:59.796
- Chet, put the phone down right now!
- Chet, put the phone down!

01:10:59.887 --> 01:11:02.401
What, are you kidding me?
This is great stuff.

01:11:04.687 --> 01:11:06.564
- And, William, stand up, please.
- But...

01:11:06.647 --> 01:11:07.921
Stand up.

01:11:08.287 --> 01:11:11.836
Now, please understand.
I am so touched by your proposal

01:11:11.927 --> 01:11:14.760
and the sweet things
that you just said to me, but...

01:11:15.167 --> 01:11:17.601
Right now is a really bad time.

01:11:17.687 --> 01:11:19.200
Do it on the show!

01:11:19.287 --> 01:11:21.198
- On the show?
- Absolutely.

01:11:21.287 --> 01:11:22.925
That's a great idea.

01:11:23.007 --> 01:11:24.042
- Really?
- CHET: Yes.

01:11:24.127 --> 01:11:26.118
And do that thing about how
every time you look at her

01:11:26.207 --> 01:11:28.277
you see the same girl
you fell in love with in high school.

01:11:28.367 --> 01:11:31.279
- What, you were listening?
- I'm in the other room, man, so, yes.

01:11:31.367 --> 01:11:34.518
And you. Hey, you!
Are you still into winning this thing?

01:11:34.607 --> 01:11:37.519
Because this is what we in the biz call
"incredible television."

01:11:37.607 --> 01:11:39.404
People are going to be
in their living rooms, sobbing.

01:11:39.487 --> 01:11:40.886
Then they're gonna be
crawling over each other

01:11:40.967 --> 01:11:43.765
trying to get to the phone
so they can call up and vote for you!

01:11:46.007 --> 01:11:50.239
Well, I'm up for it if you are, Sally.

01:11:50.327 --> 01:11:51.601
Yes! This guy!

01:11:51.687 --> 01:11:53.279
We are gonna get into this
with the producers.

01:11:53.367 --> 01:11:55.039
Can I see that ring for a second?

01:11:55.127 --> 01:11:56.526
Wow, that's great.

01:11:56.687 --> 01:11:58.518
We're gonna get a bigger one
so that it plays on TV,

01:11:58.607 --> 01:11:59.960
but there is nothing wrong with that ring.

01:12:00.047 --> 01:12:01.400
Now, here's what I'm thinking, okay?

01:12:01.487 --> 01:12:03.079
It's gonna be a special
built around the wedding.

01:12:03.167 --> 01:12:04.600
- Do you sing at all, William?
- I can sing a little bit.

01:12:04.687 --> 01:12:05.881
I thought you could sing a little bit.

01:12:05.967 --> 01:12:08.481
I think we're gonna call it
"Sally and William, sealed with a kiss."

01:12:08.567 --> 01:12:09.920
- What do you think about that?
- I love that.

01:12:10.007 --> 01:12:12.362
Yeah, I think everyone's gonna love that.

01:12:46.047 --> 01:12:47.321
Hey, Omer?

01:12:48.047 --> 01:12:49.765
Can I buy you a beer?

01:12:50.047 --> 01:12:53.357
Oh, no, no, no, no. I do not drink.
But thank you.

01:12:59.007 --> 01:13:02.841
Hey, do you ever wonder why you're doing
this whole competition thing for?

01:13:04.527 --> 01:13:06.119
Only every day.

01:13:10.807 --> 01:13:12.957
But then I think of my mother.

01:13:13.807 --> 01:13:16.037
She loved all types of singing.

01:13:17.247 --> 01:13:19.124
It keeps me going on.

01:13:25.847 --> 01:13:27.758
When I was 10 years old,

01:13:28.887 --> 01:13:30.605
I weighed 200 pounds.

01:13:32.607 --> 01:13:35.041
- That is large.
- Yeah.

01:13:37.967 --> 01:13:42.643
And I told myself I would lose 90 pounds
by the time I turned 14 or I would kill myself.

01:13:45.167 --> 01:13:46.680
So I lost the weight.

01:13:47.047 --> 01:13:48.321
And...

01:13:49.727 --> 01:13:51.922
I suddenly was really popular.

01:13:52.007 --> 01:13:56.159
I had a whole new group of friends.
I had this cute boyfriend.

01:13:56.567 --> 01:13:58.876
Even my teachers liked me better.

01:13:59.847 --> 01:14:01.678
And my mom and I
walked around the entire house

01:14:01.767 --> 01:14:05.521
collecting all the pictures of me
when I was fat and burned them.

01:14:08.447 --> 01:14:09.926
I love my mom.

01:14:16.727 --> 01:14:18.001
So.

01:14:19.567 --> 01:14:21.046
Good luck tomorrow.

01:14:22.327 --> 01:14:23.601
Thank you.

01:14:25.367 --> 01:14:27.676
Sorry I'm gonna have to destroy you.

01:14:50.287 --> 01:14:52.198
Here is your chewing gum.

01:14:52.727 --> 01:14:54.763
Remember, no blowing bubbles.

01:15:00.327 --> 01:15:02.283
Is this really necessary?

01:15:02.367 --> 01:15:06.076
Just a little bit higher. Oh, that's good.

01:15:07.287 --> 01:15:10.597
Yeah, that's beautiful.
Give me a little bit more in here.

01:15:10.687 --> 01:15:12.757
Take my moustache down a little bit, too.

01:15:16.487 --> 01:15:18.955
SHAZZY: My cousin's gonna be in the finale.

01:15:31.607 --> 01:15:33.006
- William?
- Yeah, yeah.

01:15:33.087 --> 01:15:34.964
Okay. Omer's gonna go on first.

01:15:35.047 --> 01:15:37.766
Then after Sally is done,
we're gonna hit you with a spotlight.

01:15:37.847 --> 01:15:40.202
Then you're gonna go onstage
and do your proposal.

01:15:40.287 --> 01:15:41.356
- Got it?
- Got it.

01:15:41.447 --> 01:15:43.836
- All right.
- It's happening.

01:15:44.927 --> 01:15:46.599
She's very excited.

01:15:46.767 --> 01:15:48.723
It's a joyful moment. Joyful.

01:15:51.127 --> 01:15:53.402
- Hi, Tweedy.
- Hi, Sally.

01:15:57.087 --> 01:16:00.636
Just wanted to say good luck tonight.

01:16:01.007 --> 01:16:02.281
Thank you.

01:16:02.447 --> 01:16:04.483
Could you just give us
a quick second, please?

01:16:04.567 --> 01:16:06.319
- Sure, no problem.
- Thank you.

01:16:11.567 --> 01:16:12.636
So.

01:16:13.767 --> 01:16:15.803
I think you're going to win.

01:16:16.847 --> 01:16:18.963
Novelty contestants
never win the whole thing.

01:16:19.047 --> 01:16:22.119
- That's why I've been helping him along.
- Thank you.

01:16:25.647 --> 01:16:27.524
Hey, is something wrong?

01:16:28.527 --> 01:16:29.642
No.

01:16:30.967 --> 01:16:33.527
I mean, nothing beyond
the usual creeping dread.

01:16:38.047 --> 01:16:41.357
All right. Well.
I'm sure you know at this point

01:16:41.447 --> 01:16:44.280
that William is supposed to propose to me
on tonight's show.

01:16:44.367 --> 01:16:45.436
Yeah.

01:16:46.367 --> 01:16:49.564
Do you think it's bad of me to accept
a proposal from a man I don't love

01:16:49.647 --> 01:16:52.320
in order to manipulate
people into voting for me?

01:16:53.447 --> 01:16:56.405
"Bad." Such a nebulous word, isn't it?

01:16:56.567 --> 01:16:59.923
You know what I think?
I think everyone wants something.

01:17:00.007 --> 01:17:01.599
William wants you.

01:17:02.167 --> 01:17:05.876
Why? Because he has this idea in his head
of what you are.

01:17:07.087 --> 01:17:11.000
I don't think he cares if it's true or not,
just so long as he keeps his fantasy alive.

01:17:11.087 --> 01:17:13.203
So I think he deserves what he gets.

01:17:13.287 --> 01:17:16.199
- He deserves to be miserable?
- Why not?

01:17:17.007 --> 01:17:18.679
You are, aren't you?

01:17:19.487 --> 01:17:22.160
Despite your newfound fame and adulation?

01:17:23.207 --> 01:17:24.242
Tweedy,

01:17:24.327 --> 01:17:28.400
I sometimes feel like you're the only person
in the whole world who really gets me.

01:17:30.647 --> 01:17:31.682
Yeah.

01:17:32.887 --> 01:17:36.038
Sometimes I look at you
and I see my own reflection.

01:17:36.687 --> 01:17:38.166
It's revolting.

01:17:39.487 --> 01:17:43.241
And attractive.

01:17:49.167 --> 01:17:50.441
Martin,

01:17:52.127 --> 01:17:56.200
I'm not physically attracted to other people,
but if you want me,

01:17:58.007 --> 01:17:59.326
I'm yours.

01:18:01.087 --> 01:18:04.875
The problem is I find that whenever
I become intimately involved

01:18:05.967 --> 01:18:07.764
with a woman I admire,

01:18:08.847 --> 01:18:11.884
it rapidly degenerates into mutual loathing.

01:18:13.247 --> 01:18:15.317
I don't want that to happen to us.

01:18:22.127 --> 01:18:23.765
Having said that...

01:18:53.727 --> 01:18:55.319
Omer, are you okay?

01:18:55.447 --> 01:18:58.325
Great. Great. Just a little nervous, I guess.

01:18:59.407 --> 01:19:01.796
- I just feel confused.
- About what?

01:19:01.927 --> 01:19:03.440
About this country.

01:19:03.527 --> 01:19:05.085
You know, there are
so many nice people here,

01:19:05.167 --> 01:19:07.727
but it does so much harm in the world.

01:19:08.087 --> 01:19:09.122
So?

01:19:09.207 --> 01:19:12.995
So, to what degree is this country
culpable for its actions?

01:19:13.487 --> 01:19:17.002
Are Americans to blame for America?
And beyond that,

01:19:17.847 --> 01:19:22.284
can causing someone else to suffer
ever truly ease one's own suffering?

01:19:22.807 --> 01:19:26.846
Omer! You're wigging out.
That bitch deserves to suffer!

01:19:27.567 --> 01:19:28.716
What bitch?

01:19:28.807 --> 01:19:30.001
Sally! Who are you talking about?

01:19:30.087 --> 01:19:31.122
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

01:19:31.207 --> 01:19:32.481
15 minutes, Omer.

01:19:32.887 --> 01:19:33.956
(SIGHING)

01:19:34.287 --> 01:19:37.040
Well, see, I think the dress works
'cause it flows nice.

01:19:37.127 --> 01:19:39.163
The dress is gonna be a hit.

01:19:41.007 --> 01:19:42.963
Hey, I'm gonna go run lines with Sally.

01:19:43.047 --> 01:19:44.241
- Well, don't be long.
- Okay.

01:19:44.327 --> 01:19:45.442
Yeah.

01:20:16.407 --> 01:20:19.001
Mr President,
it's such an honour to have you here.

01:20:19.087 --> 01:20:20.679
Happy to be here.

01:20:55.567 --> 01:20:59.355
"Press here to explode yourself."

01:21:01.927 --> 01:21:05.158
Where's Martin? Where the hell is Martin?
Has anybody seen Martin?

01:21:05.247 --> 01:21:08.398
- He's in there.
- What the hell is he doing in there?

01:21:09.047 --> 01:21:11.607
- What are you doing?
- This isn't pretty.

01:21:11.687 --> 01:21:12.722
What?

01:21:19.447 --> 01:21:22.359
- That's Sally and Mr Tweed?
- Yep.

01:21:31.447 --> 01:21:33.915
- Are you seeing anybody?
- What?

01:21:39.767 --> 01:21:42.156
It looks so much bigger on TV.

01:21:42.607 --> 01:21:44.199
Hey, watch my foot, huh?

01:21:46.807 --> 01:21:50.163
- So, do you feel filthy?
- Not really.

01:21:51.127 --> 01:21:52.685
How do you feel?

01:21:57.807 --> 01:21:59.126
It's weird.

01:22:00.807 --> 01:22:03.605
- I don't actually loathe you.
- You, either.

01:22:16.567 --> 01:22:18.683
Right. The President here yet?

01:22:18.807 --> 01:22:20.877
ANNOUNCER: Yeah!
How you doing, everybody?

01:22:23.927 --> 01:22:26.964
How many Omer fans
do I have with me tonight?

01:22:27.727 --> 01:22:28.842
Yeah!

01:22:30.247 --> 01:22:34.081
And how many Sally fans do I have?
She can hear you in the back!

01:22:37.367 --> 01:22:41.519
ANNOUNCER: And now your host,
Martin Tweed!

01:22:41.647 --> 01:22:43.365
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

01:22:50.407 --> 01:22:52.079
That's Martin Tweed.

01:22:52.967 --> 01:22:55.356
You're looking very good, sir. Very good.

01:22:57.567 --> 01:22:59.876
Welcome, America.

01:23:00.447 --> 01:23:03.439
Welcome, world. Welcome, everyone else.

01:23:04.447 --> 01:23:05.880
- Boo!
- AUDIENCE: Boo!

01:23:09.567 --> 01:23:11.842
We've been through so much together.

01:23:11.927 --> 01:23:15.681
We've laughed. We've cried.
We've formed attachments.

01:23:16.847 --> 01:23:19.315
And now, we're down to just two.

01:23:19.447 --> 01:23:22.803
And to help me help you judge tonight,

01:23:22.887 --> 01:23:25.117
we're welcoming a very special guest.

01:23:25.327 --> 01:23:28.000
The President of this great country,

01:23:28.727 --> 01:23:31.764
President Joseph Staton!

01:23:35.647 --> 01:23:38.002
Thanks for having me on your show.

01:23:47.127 --> 01:23:48.401
So.

01:23:48.487 --> 01:23:51.797
What do you think of these
two great contestants, Mr President?

01:23:52.407 --> 01:23:56.525
I think they exhibit
what's best about America.

01:23:58.447 --> 01:24:01.245
- The spirit of resolve...
- The spirit of resolve

01:24:01.327 --> 01:24:04.637
that makes this
the greatest country in the world.

01:24:06.807 --> 01:24:07.922
They know what they want...

01:24:08.007 --> 01:24:10.362
They know what they want
and they go out and get it.

01:24:10.447 --> 01:24:11.641
All right.

01:24:13.047 --> 01:24:16.164
- I'll be right back!
- Omer! Where are you going?

01:24:22.807 --> 01:24:24.160
(STATIC BUZZING)

01:24:24.967 --> 01:24:27.322
Where's that interference coming from?

01:24:27.607 --> 01:24:29.563
Turn that frigging thing off!

01:24:29.647 --> 01:24:31.877
And turn that frigging thing off!

01:24:33.647 --> 01:24:34.875
Oh!

01:24:43.567 --> 01:24:45.717
Okay. Okay.

01:24:46.807 --> 01:24:49.037
America, Mr President,

01:24:49.367 --> 01:24:54.157
without further ado, let me introduce
America's favourite Middle Eastern import,

01:24:54.807 --> 01:24:57.116
Omer Obeidi!

01:25:20.407 --> 01:25:22.159
Where the hell is he?

01:25:22.287 --> 01:25:24.164
- I don't know where he is...
- I'm going on!

01:25:24.727 --> 01:25:25.762
(STATIC BUZZING)

01:25:34.167 --> 01:25:35.919
SHAZZY: Go, Omer!

01:25:39.287 --> 01:25:41.847
My wife loves this guy.

01:25:44.167 --> 01:25:48.399
(SINGING) And now the end is near

01:25:50.087 --> 01:25:53.363
That's a bad call. That's Frank's song.
People aren't gonna respond to that.

01:25:53.887 --> 01:25:55.605
Bold choice of song.

01:25:56.327 --> 01:25:57.646
My friends

01:25:58.527 --> 01:26:00.597
I'll say it clear

01:26:01.607 --> 01:26:04.075
I'll state my case

01:26:04.527 --> 01:26:07.041
Of which I'm certain

01:26:08.367 --> 01:26:12.724
I've lived a life that's full

01:26:13.647 --> 01:26:15.638
I've travelled each

01:26:16.527 --> 01:26:19.678
And every highway

01:26:20.487 --> 01:26:23.877
But more, much more than this

01:26:23.967 --> 01:26:25.082
(STATIC BUZZING)

01:26:25.167 --> 01:26:26.725
I did it

01:26:27.447 --> 01:26:31.326
My way

01:26:32.767 --> 01:26:37.158
I've loved, I've laughed and cried

01:26:37.807 --> 01:26:39.763
I've had my fill

01:26:39.847 --> 01:26:41.883
Mr President, what are you doing?

01:26:41.967 --> 01:26:43.286
My share of losing

01:26:43.367 --> 01:26:45.927
I'm getting a lot of feedback in this thing.

01:26:46.007 --> 01:26:49.477
And now, as tears subside

01:26:50.087 --> 01:26:52.157
I find it all

01:26:53.247 --> 01:26:55.283
So amusing

01:26:56.687 --> 01:26:58.245
To think

01:26:59.087 --> 01:27:01.362
I did all that

01:27:01.927 --> 01:27:04.316
And may I say

01:27:05.287 --> 01:27:08.279
Not in a shy way

01:27:08.807 --> 01:27:10.320
Oh, no

01:27:11.087 --> 01:27:13.078
Oh, no, not me

01:27:13.647 --> 01:27:15.239
I did it

01:27:15.967 --> 01:27:19.243
My way

01:27:19.487 --> 01:27:22.877
For what is a man?

01:27:23.247 --> 01:27:25.238
What has he got?

01:27:26.207 --> 01:27:29.005
If not himself

01:27:29.207 --> 01:27:30.720
then he has naught

01:27:30.807 --> 01:27:32.684
William Williams, you're a moron.

01:27:33.167 --> 01:27:37.319
A moron. You stupid moron! Stupid moron!

01:27:38.247 --> 01:27:41.319
And not the words

01:27:41.407 --> 01:27:44.524
Of one who kneels

01:27:44.607 --> 01:27:47.167
The record shows

01:27:47.367 --> 01:27:49.801
I took the blows

01:27:50.047 --> 01:27:52.242
And did it

01:27:52.327 --> 01:27:57.082
My way

01:28:02.247 --> 01:28:03.805
I love you, Mom.

01:28:08.607 --> 01:28:10.199
He nailed it!

01:28:11.607 --> 01:28:13.199
That's my cousin!

01:28:13.287 --> 01:28:14.640
(STATIC BUZZING)

01:28:24.367 --> 01:28:25.959
We're gonna stand up.

01:28:37.887 --> 01:28:39.923
Omer, meet the President.

01:28:40.687 --> 01:28:42.120
OMER: Nice to meet you, sir.

01:28:42.207 --> 01:28:43.925
He's talking to him.

01:28:45.607 --> 01:28:48.565
What'd you think of Omer tonight,
Mr President?

01:28:48.807 --> 01:28:50.399
What did I think?

01:28:52.687 --> 01:28:53.915
Mr President?

01:28:54.007 --> 01:28:55.076
What did I think?

01:28:55.167 --> 01:28:57.362
Mr President? Can you read me?

01:28:58.407 --> 01:28:59.840
I think

01:29:03.167 --> 01:29:04.520
I liked you.

01:29:05.127 --> 01:29:06.446
Thank you, sir.

01:29:06.527 --> 01:29:07.960
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

01:29:08.487 --> 01:29:09.806
Go ahead.

01:29:11.327 --> 01:29:12.362
Do it!

01:29:12.447 --> 01:29:14.483
And I just want to say,

01:29:14.847 --> 01:29:16.917
in terms of the Middle East,

01:29:19.007 --> 01:29:22.841
that it looks like the problems over there
are never going to be solved.

01:29:23.727 --> 01:29:24.876
What?

01:29:25.167 --> 01:29:26.441
I mean never.

01:29:27.007 --> 01:29:29.521
Never, never, never, never, never.

01:29:30.687 --> 01:29:31.961
And so,

01:29:34.487 --> 01:29:36.284
I'm sorry about that.

01:29:36.367 --> 01:29:38.835
What the hell was that? I never said that!

01:29:38.927 --> 01:29:40.519
Oh, Poopie.

01:29:45.247 --> 01:29:46.760
Mr President?

01:29:47.727 --> 01:29:49.479
I deeply hope,

01:29:50.327 --> 01:29:52.079
for all of our sakes,

01:29:53.007 --> 01:29:54.406
that you are wrong.

01:29:55.127 --> 01:29:56.640
I hope so, too.

01:29:59.247 --> 01:30:00.680
Nice singing.

01:30:02.847 --> 01:30:03.996
Well...

01:30:04.367 --> 01:30:05.720
On a brighter note,

01:30:05.807 --> 01:30:09.117
we'll be back after a short break
with the enchanting Sally Kendoo.

01:30:09.207 --> 01:30:13.758
And then you all will decide
who is the winner of American Dreamz.

01:30:18.647 --> 01:30:21.241
That's it! Show is over!

01:30:21.327 --> 01:30:23.397
What are you talking about?
There's another contestant.

01:30:23.487 --> 01:30:24.681
Sorry, I'm taking my guy out!

01:30:24.767 --> 01:30:27.486
Your guy, your guy just went
way off reservation!

01:30:27.567 --> 01:30:30.161
Talk about depressing.
Half the audience want to shoot themselves!

01:30:30.247 --> 01:30:31.885
And you, sir, are no Oprah!

01:30:31.967 --> 01:30:34.606
I'd kind of like to see how Sally does.

01:30:34.967 --> 01:30:37.800
All right, you. Where is the you-know-what?

01:30:39.207 --> 01:30:41.846
STAGE MANAGER: And we're back
in three, two.

01:30:41.927 --> 01:30:43.406
Get off the stage! Get off the stage!

01:30:43.487 --> 01:30:44.840
We're back!

01:30:44.927 --> 01:30:48.442
And now all the way from Padookie, Ohio,

01:30:48.567 --> 01:30:52.321
America's newest sweetheart, Sally Kendoo!

01:31:21.447 --> 01:31:24.519
Where the hell is William?
He's supposed to be up here.

01:31:27.727 --> 01:31:31.959
I would like to dedicate this song
to someone very special in the audience,

01:31:32.327 --> 01:31:33.806
my boyfriend.

01:31:34.447 --> 01:31:35.926
William Williams!

01:31:51.127 --> 01:31:52.446
What? No!

01:31:52.807 --> 01:31:55.321
No, he's supposed to propose
after she sings!

01:31:55.407 --> 01:31:57.318
- He's an idiot!
- Yeah.

01:31:58.687 --> 01:32:01.406
Excuse me a moment.
This moron's missed his cue.

01:32:04.007 --> 01:32:06.601
Let's all welcome Sally's sweetheart.

01:32:06.847 --> 01:32:09.566
Decorated war veteran, William Williams!

01:32:13.807 --> 01:32:17.197
I think, perhaps, William has something
he wants to ask Sally.

01:32:18.407 --> 01:32:19.556
Sally?

01:32:21.287 --> 01:32:22.720
Yes, William?

01:32:23.367 --> 01:32:25.403
How could you do this to me?

01:32:29.007 --> 01:32:31.362
How could I do what to you?

01:32:32.647 --> 01:32:35.036
How could you sleep with Mr Tweed?

01:32:35.127 --> 01:32:36.640
(AUDIENCE GASPING)

01:32:41.927 --> 01:32:42.962
Whoa!

01:32:43.847 --> 01:32:44.916
- Boo!
- AUDIENCE: Boo!

01:32:45.007 --> 01:32:46.235
I'm serious.

01:32:47.007 --> 01:32:48.725
Well, seriously, William,

01:32:48.807 --> 01:32:51.082
I think it's common knowledge
I would never ever, ever, ever

01:32:51.167 --> 01:32:53.237
sleep with a contestant
on American Dreamz.

01:32:53.327 --> 01:32:55.397
I saw you through the keyhole.

01:32:58.407 --> 01:32:59.760
He nailed her?

01:33:02.287 --> 01:33:04.642
I guess you two think I'm stupid.

01:33:05.327 --> 01:33:08.000
I guess you all think I'm stupid.

01:33:08.767 --> 01:33:11.327
Well, I'll show you how stupid I am.

01:33:11.887 --> 01:33:15.084
I'm going to blow myself up
with this bomb I found.

01:33:15.167 --> 01:33:16.680
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

01:33:19.447 --> 01:33:22.757
William, don't joke around
about something like that.

01:33:22.847 --> 01:33:24.678
Oh, I am not joking!

01:33:24.767 --> 01:33:26.120
(AUDIENCE EXCLAIMING)

01:33:27.087 --> 01:33:28.520
What the fuck?

01:33:28.967 --> 01:33:31.765
Great idea! On-air proposal, Chet Krogl!

01:33:31.887 --> 01:33:33.161
Keep rolling! Keep rolling!

01:33:33.247 --> 01:33:35.715
Get back to your camera!
Get back to your camera!

01:33:35.807 --> 01:33:37.286
Come back! Come back!

01:33:37.527 --> 01:33:39.085
MARTIN: Get back to that camera!

01:33:39.167 --> 01:33:40.646
Oh, no.

01:33:40.847 --> 01:33:42.360
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

01:33:48.967 --> 01:33:50.286
Mr Williams?

01:33:50.767 --> 01:33:54.521
Mr Williams, do not do this.
It is not worth it.

01:33:55.247 --> 01:33:57.807
Your death will not solve any problems.

01:33:57.887 --> 01:34:00.879
It'll solve the problem
of me feeling miserable.

01:34:03.047 --> 01:34:05.607
William? I'm the President.

01:34:07.127 --> 01:34:09.004
I know who you are, sir.

01:34:09.647 --> 01:34:11.399
Now, as your Commander in Chief,

01:34:11.567 --> 01:34:14.764
I'm gonna have to ask you
not to blow yourself up.

01:34:16.127 --> 01:34:18.766
Now, I've had dark days myself, William.

01:34:19.407 --> 01:34:23.082
Days where I just wanted to lie in bed
and dream.

01:34:24.327 --> 01:34:25.726
Never get up.

01:34:29.567 --> 01:34:31.797
But I have come to think

01:34:31.967 --> 01:34:34.845
that it is better to deal with reality,

01:34:38.687 --> 01:34:40.837
no matter how unpleasant it is.

01:34:42.647 --> 01:34:44.080
That's my guy.

01:34:50.287 --> 01:34:51.879
No disrespect, sir.

01:34:53.567 --> 01:34:57.003
But if I can't have Sally Kendoo
then I don't want to go on living.

01:34:57.087 --> 01:34:58.156
(AUDIENCE CLAMOURING)

01:34:58.247 --> 01:34:59.475
William, wait...

01:34:59.847 --> 01:35:01.678
Stay there! Stay there!

01:35:04.127 --> 01:35:06.436
