(STATIC BUZZING)

01:35:52.607 --> 01:35:53.642
(EXPLOSION)

01:35:58.007 --> 01:35:59.486
What happened?

01:36:35.767 --> 01:36:37.962
Yes! Yes! Yes!

01:36:39.007 --> 01:36:41.396
You won this thing. You won it.

01:36:41.487 --> 01:36:42.920
SHAZZY: Where are you going?

01:36:43.007 --> 01:36:45.760
Listen, those three gentlemen right there.
They were the ones with the bombs.

01:36:45.847 --> 01:36:48.520
OMER: You see? Back there, those three.
They were the ones with the bomb.

01:36:56.887 --> 01:36:58.161
Go!

01:37:01.007 --> 01:37:04.204
Mr President! Stop! Stop!

01:37:18.007 --> 01:37:20.567
All right, everyone, please. Please, shut up.

01:37:21.967 --> 01:37:23.400
It's starting.

01:37:24.647 --> 01:37:28.925
SALLY: Last season's finale was
the highest-rated show in television history,

01:37:29.007 --> 01:37:31.202
as my boyfriend, William Williams,

01:37:31.287 --> 01:37:34.438
suffering from hallucinations
caused by posttraumatic stress

01:37:34.527 --> 01:37:36.245
tragically lost his life.

01:37:36.767 --> 01:37:38.564
There was a silver lining, though,

01:37:38.647 --> 01:37:42.037
as he was voted the surprise winner
of American Dreamz.

01:37:42.407 --> 01:37:44.796
I know he would have been so thrilled.

01:37:45.167 --> 01:37:46.759
Fellow runner-up, Omer Obeidi,

01:37:46.847 --> 01:37:50.635
has been touring the country
with a repertory of Broadway hits.

01:37:50.887 --> 01:37:54.163
(SINGING) Go, Greased Lightning
You're burning up the quarter mile

01:37:54.247 --> 01:37:56.477
CHORUS: Greased Lighting
Go, Greased Lighting

01:37:56.567 --> 01:37:59.240
IQBAL: Stop! Stop! Stop!

01:37:59.647 --> 01:38:01.239
This isn't a hoedown!

01:38:01.727 --> 01:38:03.797
SALLY: Special guest judge,
President Staton,

01:38:03.887 --> 01:38:06.447
recently returned
from a Mid-East fact-finding tour

01:38:06.527 --> 01:38:08.165
with his new Chief of Staff.

01:38:08.247 --> 01:38:09.885
You choose first, Poopie.

01:38:10.327 --> 01:38:11.362
(SIGHING)

01:38:11.447 --> 01:38:13.677
I guess I'll go for the newspapers first.

01:38:13.767 --> 01:38:17.919
You take the intelligence reports
and summit briefing and then we'll switch.

01:38:18.007 --> 01:38:21.363
SALLY: And I have
some pretty big shoes to fill.

01:38:21.487 --> 01:38:22.761
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

01:38:23.207 --> 01:38:24.640
Welcome!

01:38:24.887 --> 01:38:28.516
Welcome back to another season
of American Dreamz.

01:38:28.607 --> 01:38:32.486
I am so excited to be your new host,
it's such a dream come true for me.

01:38:33.087 --> 01:38:37.399
And I'd like to dedicate this season
to someone who was very special to us all.

01:38:37.967 --> 01:38:40.527
The great Mr Martin Tweed.

01:38:42.247 --> 01:38:43.600
(AUDIENCE SIGHING)

01:38:44.447 --> 01:38:47.007
We will miss you so very much.

01:38:48.047 --> 01:38:51.198
But now, on to an exciting new season!

